<h1>üé™ Events</h1>
<p>
  In Evy, <strong>event handlers</strong> react to events like keyboard input (<code>on key</code>).
</p>
<details>
  <summary>Docs</summary>
  <p>
    An event handler starts with <code>on</code>, then the event type, parameters, code, and ends
    with <code>end</code>. This example prints the pressed key:
  </p>
  <pre><code class="language-evy">on key k:string
  print k
end
</code></pre>
  <p><code>k:string</code> is the parameter (must be a string).</p>
  <p>
    There are six types of events in Evy: <code>key</code>, <code>down</code>, <code>up</code>,
    <code>move</code>, <code>animate</code>, and <code>input</code>.
  </p>
</details>
